## Polish (Architect mandate)

- **Smooth easing on torch decay** — linear decay with cubic-in-out perceptual mapping in the overlay, so darkness rises slowly at first and accelerates through the danger zone (not stair-step).
- **Considered overlay gradient** — vertical indigo gradient (sky → horizon → sky) plus a corner vignette (tunnel-vision feel), not flat black.
- **Torch flicker animation** — two-frequency sine flicker on player torch (~7.3 Hz + 13.1 Hz overtone) and campfire light (~4.7 Hz + 9.2 Hz overtone) so adjacent flames don't pulse in lockstep.
- **Edge cases handled inline** —
  - `torchAmount` undefined → defaults to 1.0, no overlay (allows Concern A standalone).
  - Player exactly on campfire boundary → soft radial gradient = no hard edge; relight uses `<=` (boundary counts as inside, generous).
  - Multiple campfires overlap → `destination-out` compounds naturally; relight loop short-circuits on first in-range fire.
  - Mode switch mid-tick → guard at top of every Night-only function returns immediately when `runtime.mode !== 'night'`.

## Verification (live browser smoke test, port 3996)

- Day Mode Stage 1 → bright (no overlay).
- Day Mode @ torch=0 forced → still bright (mode guard intact).
- Night Mode Stage 1 → overlay engages as `torchAmount` drops; campfire near spawn keeps player lit (relight works).
- Night Mode @ torch=0, player moved to corner → full screen darkness with glowing player torch hole + campfire glow at base.
- Stat scaling sanity: lurker base hp 10 → 14 after night-spawn, base dmg 5 → 7. Ratio 1.40 confirmed.

## Spec deviation noted

The worker spec mentions `hunt-pickups.js` as a place to spawn Torch items at chopped-tree positions. That module's existing scope is ad-gated weapon-pickup platforms (modal flow, locked sprites). All other field drops (coin/wood/orb/fragment) live in `hunt-player.js` via `runtime.drops` + `pickupTick`, so the Torch field-drop follows that pattern for symmetry. `hunt-pickups.js` untouched.

## Working-tree state at handoff

`hunt-render.js` and `hunt-player.js` carry uncommitted changes from another worker (W-Turret-And-Campfire-Combat — drawBuiltStructures, DOM levelup modal rewrite, constructionTick, etc.). Per the Hive rule "Don't push another Claude's work without asking," those hunks were NOT committed by this worker — only the Day/Night + Torch hunks land in HEAD. The other worker's WIP remains in the working tree for whoever picks it up.
